                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Exalt the Little Ones",
            "subtype": "ability",
            "text": "The arboreal shepherd encourages its friends to overcome titanic odds. For 1 round, allies with the animal trait in a 50-foot radius gain a +1 status bonus to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws. If the animals have the swarm trait, the saving throw DCs to resist their damaging actions gain a +1 status bonus. This bonus increases to +2 for allies whose level is 2 or lower.",
            "traits": [
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 16,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "84c09922ddd30f2144494f2cb6f19412",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Auditory",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 453",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 453,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Auditory actions and effects rely on sound. An action with the auditory trait can be successfully performed only if the creature using the action can speak or otherwise produce the required sounds. A spell or effect with the auditory trait has its effect only if the target can hear it. This applies only to sound-based parts of the effect, as determined by the GM. This is different from a sonic effect, which still affects targets who can\u2019t hear it (such as deaf targets) as long as the effect itself makes sound.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 101,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "c1c0a189dd3d1a3d7c5daf9a6bafba49",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Linguistic",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 458,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "An effect with this trait depends on language comprehension. A linguistic effect that targets a creature works only if the target understands the language you are using.",
                "type": "trait"
              },
              {
                "alternate_link": {
                  "alternate_type": "legacy",
                  "aonid": 134,
                  "game-obj": "Traits",
                  "type": "alternate_link"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "game-id": "60a4f011afd1e0fac8211bd01108d104",
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "name": "Primal",
                "sources": [
                  {
                    "errata": {
                      "alt": "2.0",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "2.0",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "link": {
                      "alt": "Player Core pg. 460",
                      "aonid": 216,
                      "game-obj": "Sources",
                      "name": "Player Core pg. 460",
                      "type": "link"
                    },
                    "name": "Player Core",
                    "page": 460,
                    "type": "source"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "This magic comes from the primal tradition, connecting to the natural world and instinct. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to primal magic.",
                "type": "trait"
              }
            ],
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
